Bayelsa State government has announced the death of another COVID-19 patient. The State COVID-19 Task Force Chairman, Dr Inodu Apoku, disclosed this in a statement on Friday in Yenagoa. According to Apoku, it was the third death from the nine new cases recorded by the state on Thursday. Recall that Bayelsa had last week recorded COVID-19 related death cases Apoku said, “One of these fresh unlinked cases was brought in critically ill and died a few minutes after admission. “Following the history of the sickness, as was revealed by relatives, samples were collected for COVID-19 testing. “She died as a COVID-19 suspected case. “The test result returned positive, and as such, we have another COVID -19 related death making a total of three deaths in the state.” These content links are provided by Content.ad. Both Content.ad and the web site upon which the links are displayed may receive compensation when readers click on these links. Some of the content you are redirected to may be sponsored content. View our privacy policy here. To learn how you can use Content.ad to drive visitors to your content or add this service to your site, please contact us at info@content.ad. Family-Friendly Content Only recommend family-friendly content Website owners select the type of content that appears in our units. However, if you would like to ensure that Content.ad always displays family-friendly content on this device, regardless of what site you are on, check the option below. Learn More